overview: The user initiated a comprehensive review of a sleep questionnaire
  application, aiming to ensure all acceptance criteria from the Statement of
  Work and detailed specification were met. The agent meticulously analyzed the
  existing codebase, identified several critical gaps, and formulated a detailed
  plan. Subsequently, the agent implemented key missing features, including a
  1-10 severity scale for tiredness with crucial safety messaging, robust
  detection and reporting for complex sleep disorders like COMISA and
  Insufficient Sleep Syndrome, and integrated valuable external resource links
  within the generated reports. Furthermore, the agent refined the Excessive
  Daytime Sleepiness (EDS) scoring to incorporate weighted criteria and
  significantly enhanced the data export functionality by expanding the CSV to
  include all flattened questionnaire responses. This systematic approach
  ensured the application now more accurately assesses sleep health and provides
  comprehensive, actionable insights.
